-- South Korean Police Officers Called in for Emergency Duty After Kim Death
-- B y   S a n g w o n   Y o o n
-- 2011-12-19T04:25:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/south-korean-police-officers-called-in-for-emergency-duty-after-kim-death.html
South Korean police officers have
been called to work for emergency duty and commanders are
discussing “a detailed course of action in response to news of
Kim Jong Il’s death,” the  National Police Agency  said in a
statement on its website. All police units have been placed on
alert, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangwon Yoon in Seoul at 
 syoon32@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
